    Scope and Contents
ILLINOIS COAL: THE LEGACY OF AN INDUSTRIAL SOCIETY
VanHooser, coal miner, discusses mining in the Taylorville area in central Illinois: mechanization in the mines, mine wars of the 1930's between the PMA and the UMW, and the impact of the mine wars on the community.1 tape, 85 mins., 31 pp.
Interview by Kevin Corley, 1986
OPEN
See collateral file: interviewer's notes and photocopies of photos, certificates and articles from the National Coal Museum.  
  
